<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She announced she's expecting her first child with boyfriend Josh Barker, earlier this month.</p>

<p>And on Tuesday, pregnant Elyse Knowles was spotted looking positively glowing during a lunch outing in Byron Bay.</p>

<p>The 27-year-old model was effortlessly chic, sporting a pretty white tank and matching shorts for the occasion.</p>

<p>She's glowing! On Tuesday, pregnant Elyse Knowles (pictured) was spotted looking positively glowing during a lunch outing in Byron Bay</p>

<p>Elyse's top revealed a hint of her tummy, which she touched tenderly.  </p>

<p>The gorgeous blonde showed off her long, tanned pins as she stepped out following the surprise baby announcement, accessorising with a pair of comfortable brown flat sandals and an orange fedora.</p>

<p>Elyse complimented her look with an over-the-shoulder bag of the same colour, and wore a pair of trendy sunglasses to shield her eyes from the spring sunshine.</p>

<p>The beauty and her boyfriend Josh have only recently returned from the Northern Territory, where they chose to announce their pregnancy news.</p>

<p>Stunning:  The 27-year-old model was effortlessly chic, sporting a pretty white tank and matching shorts for the occasion. Elyse's top revealed a hint of her tummy, which she touched tenderly</p>

<p>Gorgeous: Elyse complimented her look with an over-the-shoulder bag of the same colour, and wore a pair of trendy sunglasses to shield her eyes from the spring sunshine </p>

<p>The model shared the joyful news to her Instagram page on Wednesday night.</p>

<p>'And then there were 3 #babybarker,' she wrote alongside a gallery of images of the couple on holiday.</p>

<p>The announcement came four months after Elyse and Josh bought a $2.3million beach house in Byron Bay.</p>

<p>Their new 1960s built property is located in the old part of Byron Bay town, just a short walk from the main beach and surrounded by tranquil greenery.</p>

<p>Baby on board: Elyse announced she is expecting her first child with boyfriend Josh Barker (both pictured) earlier this month </p>

<p>Last year, Elyse told Daily Mail Australia that the couple had moved to Byron Bay from Melbourne while chasing a more sustainable lifestyle for themselves.</p>

<p>Speaking at an event in September, the model explained she'd physically confront strangers that she would see littering in Victoria, before eventually leaving.</p>

<p>She explained: 'I just can't see it being left on the ground and when they're dropping rubbish, I think they need to be told off.'</p>

